    {
        "content": "<p>avanhatt opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12717\">PR #12717</a> from <code>avanhatt:ty-params-3-4</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Discussed in issue <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12716\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12716</a>. </p>\n<p>Right now in ISLE, most clif instructions have a type parameter in opt for the midend, but not in lowering (e.g., <code>iadd ty x y)</code> vs <code>(iadd x y)</code>. From our previous discussions (@cfallin @fitzgen), this is mostly due to the order of implementation rather than a design decision. For our verification work, it's useful to also have the type parameters in the lowering terms, as well, if they produce values (e.g., excluding things like <code>store</code>). </p>\n<p>This changes uses scripting to automatically change the many relevant rules, by programmatically adding <code>_</code>. Over time, we can update rules to remove now-simplifiable <code>has_ty</code> terms.</p>\n<p>This is based on an earlier commit/script from @mmcloughlin , with changes to merge into upstream after #10524.<br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 577316601,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1772645405
    },
